  "prompt": "What is the weather in Orlando like on June, and how does it differ from the weather in August?",
  "response": "Orlando weather in June and August is both hot and humid, but there are some key differences:\n\n**June Weather in Orlando:**\n\n*   **Temperature:** Highs typically reach the low 90s Fahrenheit (around 32-34\u00b0C). Lows are usually in the low 70s Fahrenheit (around 22-23\u00b0C).\n*   **Humidity:** Very high. Expect sticky and uncomfortable conditions.\n*   **Rainfall:** June marks the beginning of the rainy season. You can expect frequent afternoon thunderstorms, but they are often brief. Average rainfall is around 7-8 inches.\n*   **Hurricane Risk:** Hurricane season officially starts in June, but the risk is generally lower than in August.\n*   **Daylight:** Longest days of the year. Plenty of sunshine.\n\n**August Weather in Orlando:**\n\n*   **Temperature:** Highs are similar to June, typically in the low 90s Fahrenheit (around 32-34\u00b0C). Lows are also similar, in the low 70s Fahrenheit (around 22-23\u00b0C).\n*   **Humidity:** Very high. The humidity can actually feel even more oppressive than in June.\n*   **Rainfall:** August is typically the rainiest month of the year in Orlando. You can expect daily afternoon thunderstorms. Average rainfall is usually higher than June, often exceeding 8 inches.\n*   **Hurricane Risk:** August is the peak of hurricane season. The risk of a tropical storm or hurricane affecting Orlando is significantly higher in August compared to June.\n*   **Daylight:** Days are starting to get slightly shorter compared to June.\n\n**Key Differences Summarized:**\n\n| Feature       | June                     | August                   |\n|---------------|--------------------------|--------------------------|\n| Temperature   | Similar to August          | Similar to June          |\n| Humidity      | Very high                | Very high, potentially more oppressive |\n| Rainfall      | High, frequent storms    | Higher, more frequent storms, often the rainiest month|\n| Hurricane Risk | Lower relative to August | Higher, peak of the season|\n| Daylight      | Longest days             | Days slightly shorter      |\n\n**In summary:**\n\n*   Both June and August are hot, humid, and rainy in Orlando.\n*   August is generally rainier and has a higher risk of hurricanes than June.\n*   The humidity can feel more intense in August due to the consistently wet conditions.\n*   If you're planning a trip and concerned about hurricanes, June is generally a safer bet than August.\n\n**Tips for Visiting Orlando in June or August:**\n\n*   **Stay Hydrated:** Drink plenty of water to combat the heat and humidity.\n*   **Wear Light Clothing:** Opt for loose-fitting, breathable fabrics.\n*   **Use Sunscreen:** Protect yourself from the strong sun.\n*   **Plan for Rain:** Be prepared for afternoon thunderstorms. Have indoor activities planned as backup.\n*   **Check the Forecast:** Keep an eye on the weather forecast, especially if traveling in August, due to the hurricane risk.\n*   **Take Breaks:** Avoid overexertion by taking frequent breaks in air-conditioned spaces.\n*   **Consider Crowd Levels:** June is before school is out, so crowds are lighter in early June. August is one of the least-crowded months, as the school year starts and people finish their summer vacations.\n",
